<subSubSection id="E6394813B5D8DE6F694F1F8755BE1081" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="type material">
<paragraph id="F2004DB767B317EDCE189465720FD695" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Type material.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D0DB465020BD754ABFB6AE03D6E55EE7" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Holotype female at MNHN, labeled 
<normalizedToken id="DDDB1DA88E9E04A0EA0C3AA21A04FC7A" originalValue="“Muséum">&quot;Museum</normalizedToken>
Paris,&quot; &quot;Madagascar, Mgn 
<normalizedToken id="D0E1B8A9AA54AA1810C7F9385906D9DD" originalValue="l’Ambre,”">l'Ambre,&quot;</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="A181E1346B54D075F61A35420298459D" originalValue="“Muséum">&quot;Museum</normalizedToken>
Paris 1.34 A. Seyrig,&quot; &quot;TYPE [red],&quot; &quot;Orthogonalys gigantea sp. n. holotype ♀, det. P. L. G. 
<bibRefCitation id="5368DE258BB681EFCA10BD83CC0DD59F" author="Benoit, PLG" journalOrPublisher="Revue de Zoologie et de Botanique Africaines" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="141 - 147" refId="B1" refString="Benoit, PLG, 1951. La systematique des Trigonaloidae (Hym.) ethiopiens. Revue de Zoologie et de Botanique Africaines 44 (2): 141 - 147" title="La systematique des Trigonaloidae (Hym.) ethiopiens." volume="44" year="1951">Benoit 1951</bibRefCitation>
.&quot; 
<bibRefCitation id="6806111FA5DB36AA986C71CFB1CB3018" author="Benoit, PLG" journalOrPublisher="Revue de Zoologie et de Botanique Africaines" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="141 - 147" refId="B1" refString="Benoit, PLG, 1951. La systematique des Trigonaloidae (Hym.) ethiopiens. Revue de Zoologie et de Botanique Africaines 44 (2): 141 - 147" title="La systematique des Trigonaloidae (Hym.) ethiopiens." volume="44" year="1951">Benoit (1951)</bibRefCitation>
described the species from &quot;Madagascar: Montagne 
<normalizedToken id="9FAA20815046BA467317FB4F7C156C84" originalValue="d’Ambre">d'Ambre</normalizedToken>
I.1934 (A. Seyrig ♀ holotype, au 
<normalizedToken id="ED5E627FDAF6C9B1889DBAD57CEEADBD" originalValue="Muséum">Museum</normalizedToken>
National 
<normalizedToken id="3C75999236A337139D61636649CCEFAF" originalValue="d’Histoire">d'Histoire</normalizedToken>
Naturelle de Paris.&quot; The antennae are missing except first three antennomeres of left and first antennomere of right and parts are glued onto a piece of cardboard on the pin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="99A0DA0BE3B94911DE9E78F3875C8854" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="additional specimen examined">
